First Lady Margaret Kenyatta on Wednesday evening received the Fellowship of Honoris Causa award from the Royal College of Obstetricians and Gynaecologists in Cape Town, South Africa.The honorary accolade was in recognition of her unflinching commitment to end maternal and child mortality in Kenya, besides her efforts to reduce mother-to-child HIV transmission through the Beyond Zero initiative.Before receiving the award, a comprehensive citation about the First Lady described her as a person who carries herself with grace, determination, commitment, focus and passion, especially when addressing the plight of women and children.The citation was made by Anne-Beatrice Kihara, president-elect of the African Federation of Obstetricians and Gynaecologists. Kenyatta thanked the RCOG fraternity for the honour. &ldquo;I&rsquo;m proud to be received as a &lsquo;Fellow Ad Eundeum&rsquo; of your illustrious institution. At the heart of this award is an implicit recognition of the Beyond Zero initiative.&rdquo;